review_blob: Hazy yellow/orange color, good head.  Carbonated with very small bubbles.  Taste is light, airy, and complex.  Masks abv extremely well.  Perhaps my all time favorite.

Pours a deep red, with no head at all other than a few bubbles floating on the surface.  Taste is complex with some acidity and vinous notes, almost like a true lambic.  Masks the abv well.  Smell is a bit lacking.  Overall a beer I will def buy again.
Excellent, almost creamy mouthfeel.  Almost a translucent light orange appearance.  Excellent beer overall, tastes very similar to Brewer's Art Pale Ale.
beer_name: Southampton Golden Valley  Trappist Pale Ale

review_blob: Lives up to expectations.  Good appearance, and incredibly complex aroma and flavor.  I prefer the 8 though, as the complexity is slightly masked by the high abv.
